{"title_page": "1948 Albanian Superliga", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition = [[Albanian Superliga]]\n| season      = 1948\n| winners     = [[Partizani Tirana|Partizani]]\n| prevseason = [[1947 Albanian Superliga|1947]]\n| nextseason = [[1949 Albanian Superliga|1949]]\n}}\nStatistics of [[Albanian Superliga]] in the 1948 season.\n\n==Overview==\nIt was contested by 14 teams, and [[Partizani Tirana|Partizani]] won the championship.\n\n==League standings==\n===Group A===\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|section=Group A\n|res_col_header=Q\n|winpoints=2\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n\n|team1=PAR|name_PAR=[[FK Partizani Tirana|Partizani]]\n|team2=VLL|name_VLL=[[KF Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia]]\n|team3=N\u00cbN|name_N\u00cbN=[[KF Tirana|17 N\u00ebntori]]\n|team4=DUR|name_DUR=[[KS Teuta Durr\u00ebs|Ylli i Kuq Durr\u00ebs]]\n|team5=BES|name_BES=[[Besa Kavaj\u00eb|Besa]]\n|team6=KOR|name_KOR=[[KF Sk\u00ebnderbeu Kor\u00e7\u00eb|Dinamo Kor\u00e7a]]\n\n|win_PAR=8|draw_PAR=1|loss_PAR=1|gf_PAR=34|ga_PAR=8|status_PAR=C\n|win_VLL=8|draw_VLL=1|loss_VLL=1|gf_VLL=26|ga_VLL=7\n|win_N\u00cbN=4|draw_N\u00cbN=2|loss_N\u00cbN=3|gf_N\u00cbN=9|ga_N\u00cbN=9\n|win_DUR=3|draw_DUR=2|loss_DUR=4|gf_DUR=12|ga_DUR=16\n|win_BES=0|draw_BES=1|loss_BES=8|gf_BES=7|ga_BES=33\n|win_KOR=0|draw_KOR=1|loss_KOR=6|gf_KOR=6|ga_KOR=33\n\n|col_Q=green1|text_Q=Qualification for the final\n|result1=Q\n|update=complete|source=[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/alba49.html rsssf.com]\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\nNote: '17 N\u00ebntori' is [[SK Tirana]], 'Ylli i Kuq Durr\u00ebs' is [[KS Teuta Durr\u00ebs]] and 'Dinamo Kor\u00e7a' is [[Sk\u00ebnderbeu]]\n\n===Group B===\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|section=Group B\n|res_col_header=QR\n|winpoints=2\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n\n|team1=FLA|name_FLA=[[Flamurtari Vlor\u00eb|Flamurtari]]\n|team2=ELB|name_ELB=[[KS Elbasani|Bashkimi Elbasanas]]\n|team3=APO|name_APO=[[KF Apolonia Fier|Apolonia]]\n|team4=SHQ|name_SHQ=[[Luft\u00ebtari Gjirokast\u00ebr|Shqiponja]]\n|team5=N\u00cbN|name_N\u00cbN=[[KF Erzeni|8 N\u00ebntori]]\n|team6=TRA|name_TRA=[[KS Lushnja|Traktori]]\n|team7=TOM|name_TOM=[[FK Tomori Berat|Tomori]]\n|team8=KU\u00c7|name_KU\u00c7=[[KF Naft\u00ebtari|Spartak Ku\u00e7ova]]\n\n|win_FLA=8|draw_FLA=4|loss_FLA=2|gf_FLA=47|ga_FLA=19\n|win_ELB=7|draw_ELB=5|loss_ELB=2|gf_ELB=34|ga_ELB=15\n|win_APO=7|draw_APO=5|loss_APO=2|gf_APO=31|ga_APO=20\n|win_SHQ=6|draw_SHQ=4|loss_SHQ=4|gf_SHQ=31|ga_SHQ=23|status_SHQ=R\n|win_N\u00cbN=5|draw_N\u00cbN=5|loss_N\u00cbN=4|gf_N\u00cbN=23|ga_N\u00cbN=25\n|win_TRA=4|draw_TRA=2|loss_TRA=8|gf_TRA=22|ga_TRA=34|status_TRA=R\n|win_TOM=3|draw_TOM=3|loss_TOM=8|gf_TOM=18|ga_TOM=32|status_TOM=R\n|win_KU\u00c7=1|draw_KU\u00c7=2|loss_KU\u00c7=11|gf_KU\u00c7=17|ga_KU\u00c7=55|status_KU\u00c7=R\n\n|col_Q=green1|text_Q=Qualification for the final\n|result1=Q\n|col_R=red1|text_R=Relegation to the [[1949 Albanian First Division|Albanian First Division]]\n|result4=R|result6=R|result7=R|result8=R\n|update=complete|source=[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/alba49.html rsssf.com]\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\nNote: 'Bashkimi Elbasanas' is [[KS Elbasani]], 'Shqiponja' is [[Luft\u00ebtari]], '8 N\u00ebntori' is [[KF Erzeni|Erzeni]], 'Traktori' is [[KS Lushnja]] and 'Spartak Ku\u00e7ova' is [[Naft\u00ebtari]]\n\n==Final==\n{{football box\n|date       = 25 August 1948\n|time       = \n|team1      = [[FK Partizani Tirana|Partizani]]\n|score      = 6\u20132\n|aet        = \n|report     = \n|team2      = [[Flamurtari Vlor\u00eb|Flamurtari]]\n|goals1     = [[Vasif Bi\u00e7aku|Bi\u00e7aku]] {{goal|25}}<br>[[Zihni Gjinali|Gjinali]] {{goal|29||43||56||72}}<br>[[Xhevdet Shaqiri|Shaqiri]] {{goal|74}}\n|goals2     = Bezhani {{goal|8}}<br>[[Tish Daija|Daija]] {{goal|88}}\n|stadium    = [[Qemal Stafa Stadium]], [[Tiran\u00eb]]\n|attendance = \n|referee    = \n}}\n\n==Interrupted Championship 1948-49==\nIn 1948 the [[Albanian Football Association|AFA]] decided to employ a new formula for  the championship, according to the 'western' calendar. For the first time in history, Albania's championship style would be compared to that of Western European countries, from autumn 1948-spring 1949;<ref>[http://www.panorama.com.al/sport/prapaskena-e-zhdukjes-se-kampionatit-te-partizanit-kampion-1948-49/ Prapaskena e zhdukjes s\u00eb kampionatit t\u00eb Partizanit \u201ckampion\u201d 1948-\u201849] - Panorama {{in lang|sq}}</ref> but on March 31st, 1949, the Federata Sportive Shqiptare (Albanian Sports Federation) annulled the 1948-49 season under Soviet pressure.<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/alba49.html RSSF Albania]</ref> After disassociating itself from all Soviet influences (December 3rd, 1961), Albania started a fall/spring season from 1962/63 on.\n\nTable at abandonment:\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|winpoints=2\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n\n|team1=PAR|name_PAR=Partizani\n|team2=TIR|name_TIR=Tirana\n|team3=SHK|name_SHK=Shkodra\n|team4=DUR|name_DUR=Durr\u00ebsi\n|team5=KAV|name_KAV=Kavaja\n|team6=KOR|name_KOR=Kor\u00e7a\n|team7=ELB|name_ELB=Elbasani\n|team8=VLO|name_VLO=Vlora\n\n|win_PAR=5|draw_PAR=1|loss_PAR=0|gf_PAR=26|ga_PAR=2\n|win_TIR=4|draw_TIR=1|loss_TIR=1|gf_TIR=10|ga_TIR=4\n|win_SHK=4|draw_SHK=0|loss_SHK=1|gf_SHK=21|ga_SHK=1\n|win_DUR=3|draw_DUR=1|loss_DUR=2|gf_DUR=8|ga_DUR=7\n|win_KAV=1|draw_KAV=1|loss_KAV=3|gf_KAV=10|ga_KAV=11\n|win_KOR=1|draw_KOR=0|loss_KOR=3|gf_KOR=7|ga_KOR=10\n|win_ELB=0|draw_ELB=2|loss_ELB=4|gf_ELB=5|ga_ELB=27\n|win_VLO=0|draw_VLO=2|loss_VLO=4|gf_VLO=2|ga_VLO=27\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\nNB: apart from the last round, the matches Kor\u00e7a vs Kavaja and Kor\u00e7a vs Shkodra were not played.\n\nAll the police (Dinamo) and trade union (Spartaku) clubs changed their name to simply the town name, apart from Partizani and Dinamo Tirana.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.giovanniarmillotta.it/albania/calcio/alba48.html Albania - List of final tables (RSSSF)]\n\n{{Albanian Superliga seasons |state=autocollapse}}\n{{1947\u201348 in European Football (UEFA)}}\n{{1948\u201349 in European Football (UEFA)}}\n\n[[Category:Albanian Superliga seasons]]\n[[Category:1948 in Albanian football|1]]\n[[Category:1948\u201349 in European association football leagues|Albania]]\n[[Category:1947\u201348 in European association football leagues|Albania]]\n\n\n{{Albania-footy-competition-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition = [[Albanian Superliga]]\n| season      = 1948\n| winners     = [[Partizani Tirana|Partizani]]\n| prevseason = [[1947 Albanian Superliga|1947]]\n| nextseason = [[1949 Albanian Superliga|1949]]\n}}\nStatistics of [[Albanian Superliga]] in the 1948 season.\n\n==Overview==\nIt was contested by 14 teams, and [[Partizani Tirana|Partizani]] won the championship.\n\n==League standings==\n===Group A===\n<onlyinclude>{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|section=Group A\n|res_col_header=Q\n|winpoints=2\n|use_goal_ratio=y\n\n|team1=PAR|name_PAR=[[FK Partizani Tirana|Partizani]]\n|team2=VLL|name_VLL=[[KF Vllaznia Shkod\u00ebr|Vllaznia]]\n|team3=N\u00cbN|name_N\u00cbN=[[KF Tirana|17 N\u00ebntori]]\n|team4=DUR|name_DUR=[[KS Teuta Durr\u00ebs|Ylli i Kuq Durr\u00ebs]]\n|team5=BES|name_BES=[[Besa Kavaj\u00eb|Besa]]\n|team6=KOR|name_KOR=[[KF Sk\u00ebnderbeu Kor\u00e7\u00eb|Dinamo Kor\u00e7a]]\n\n|win_PAR=8|draw_PAR=1|loss_PAR=1|gf_PAR=34|ga_PAR=8|status_PAR=C\n|win_VLL=8|draw_VLL=1|loss_VLL=1|gf_VLL=26|ga_VLL=7\n|win_N\u00cbN=4|draw_N\u00cbN=2|loss_N\u00cbN=3|gf_N\u00cbN=9|ga_N\u00cbN=9\n|win_DUR=3|draw_DUR=2|loss_DUR=4|gf_DUR=12|ga_DUR=16\n|win_BES=0|draw_BES=1|loss_BES=8|gf_BES=7|ga_BES=33\n|win_KOR=0|draw_KOR=1|loss_KOR=6|gf_KOR=6|ga_KOR=33\n\n|col_Q=green1|text_Q=Qualification for the final\n|result1=Q|\n|update=complete|source=[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesa/alba49.html rsssf.com]\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\nNote: '17 N\u00ebntori' is [[SK Tirana]], 'Ylli i Kuq Durr\u00ebs' is [[KS Teuta Durr\u00ebs]] and 'Dinamo Kor\u00e7a' is [[Sk\u00ebnderbeu]]\n\n=